Michigan Business School Names First Female Dean, WSJ Says

-- B y   H e a t h e r   B u r k e
-- 
2011-02-15T22:16:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/michigan-business-school-names-first-female-dean-wsj-says.html
  University of Michigan ’s Ross School
of Business named Alison Davis-Blake as its first female dean,
the Wall Street Journal reported.  Davis-Blake, currently dean of University of Minnesota’s
Carlson School of Management, replaces Robert Dolan in August,
the newspaper said. Women comprised about 18 percent of all
deans in the 2009-2010 school year at business schools
accredited by the Advance Collegiate Schools of Business, the
Journal said.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
